SIMPLE: part-time
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: part-time
<hw>part-time</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Occupying less than
the entire time appropriate to an activity; <as>as, a <ex>part-time</ex>
job</as>. Opposed to <ant>full-time</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Employed for less than the full time usually
expended at a task or occupation; <as>as, <ex>part-time</ex> employees;
a <ex>part-time</ex> teacher</as>. Opposed to <ant>full-time</ant>.
Commonly, thirty-five hours per week or more is considered full-time,
and less than 30 is <ex>part-time</ex> work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>part-time</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: part-time
<hw>part-time</hw> <pos>adv.</pos> <def>For less than the usual full
time appropriate to an activity; on a part-time basis; <as>as, to sell
real estate <ex>part-time</ex></as>. Opposed to
<ant>full-time</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>part-time</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: part-time
<hw>part-time</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A working schedule occupying less
than full time, i.e. less than 35 hours per week.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> part time.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>part-timer</ent>⟦br⟧
